<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="376" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.156/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-10T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 10,
                                        1917—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>You are instructed to use your informal good offices with Paraguayan
                            Government to obtain an extension of the contract of the Construction
                            and Engineering Finance Company, which, owing to the war, has been
                            unable to finance and obtain material for construction of port and dock
                            system.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>